track_notes: Room to park roadside, approached from south in icy road conditions - road does not get gritted beyond the village seemingly. Advised by locals that approaching by car from the north in winter is not advised due to steep hairpin on hill. Walked in snow so path not detectable. Transit time from car to summit was 50 mins in lying snow.
Plenty of parking in the caving club car park at SN 855 155
Link route between the two summits
Enough room to park 5 cars at the start, quite boggy in places through-out the winter season, but a lovely hike in summer time!
track_title: Fan Nedd GW/SW-007 followed by Fan Gyhirych GW/SW-007
